Thinking about this, I agree there isn't a lot more us paladin's really need.    I would expect with the Planes of Power coming up, paladins will get some more spells, hopefully some to fill in the 51-56 gaps of having few new spells.  However, it will likely be a bunch more lvl 60 spells.   <br>
<br>
1) Changing Divine Vigor to a group based 100HP buff would not be unbalancing or a problem.   Essentially a lower version of the Brells mountainous barrier, and not bad for the level difference from Divine Glory...(did I swap those two?  i always get the names mixed up)<br>
<br>
2) Change ToK to a max 4 mobs, PBAoE stun spell.   yes, this would generate agro, however, it would be nice to help an enchanter when they are having Mez problems, or when root breaks and 1-2 mobs head for your healers.   I don't think it would be hugely unbalancing, doesn't need damage or even last more than 1 second.<br>
<br>
3) as for disciplines.....I leave that to people who get to use them more often.   I recently just got to 55 and Holyforge, and have not fought undead yet, so can't comment on it or the sanctification disc.<br>
<br>
4) I agree Superior healing should be a bit lower in level...54 or 55??   <br>
<br>
5) I think as a Paladin, it would be useful, but possibly unbalancing to have a couple other group buff spells.   Examples are below:<br>
<br>
Group Yaulp IV?   I always thought Yaulp should be given to paladins BEFORE clerics since we are the ones fighting.  I also think the yaulp line should be moved down the level rung so around 56 or so we are using yaulp IV.   Of course, I think we should have a better yaulp at 60.    group Yaulp would be nice since it benefits everyone, and would be nice to boost the other melee's<br>
<br>
Group resistance?  Something like a 10 second to 20 second duration spell which increases the resistances to magic, or fire / cold or some combination.   It would have limited use, but would help buff the group from AoE's...granted HWoP does great, it would be a nice upgrade I think.<br>
<br>
<br>
That is all I can think of right now.    Some are just ideas I think would be nice to have, but not required.   I just think Paladins should be holy warrior Spurring their friends and combat on in battle.<br>
<br>
wyrmbane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucylria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cylria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 142<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/5/02 11:44:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15162.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pallies</span><hr size=1> As I've always said, every class &quot;needs&quot; something, balanced or not. There will be upgrades in PoP, and possibly in some patches before or after. Any class that doesn't see anything new will soon fall behind and become underpowered.<br>
<br>
I don't feel we should or will get any kind of undead snare. Kiting really doesn't seem to be something VI is happy about. A slow vs undead would be nice, but personally I'd rather see paladins get more spells/skills/abilties that are usefull against more forms of evil, not just undead.<br>
<br>
I haven't seen very much of the high end game, but I seem to be the only person who thinks Thuner of Karana should be put back the way it was. Riddle me this:<br>
<br>
About the time Luclin came out, VI implemented a system that letsthem make MoBs immune to any specific spell they desired. ToK made certain MoBs too easy if 3+ paladins where available to shut down its spellcasting. <br>
<br>
Would it be reasonalbe to flag any MoB that is likely to be taken on by more than one group (aka raid level) immune to this spell? In big raid zones this spell can even be disabled completely. That would make ToK only really useable in exp groups where you'll rarely see more than 3 paladins.<br>
<br>
I'm not at the point in EQ where I could use this spell, so don't flame me. I'm just curious since people have been saying that this spell was fine in exp groups. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uabbak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Abbak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/5/02 1:58:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15162.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pallies</span><hr size=1> They need to balance 1hs/shield combo to 2hs weapons... <br>
